{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"66efebcf-7f13-4bf1-a9d1-2359ec7bb0a2","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Register your package on nuget.org for trusted publishing\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a **GitHub Actions** publisher: set your repo owner, repo name, branch/tag pattern, and optionally the workflow filename and environment\n\n### 2. Update your workflow\n\n**Remove:**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push ... --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n```\n\n**Add these changes:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    # Required for OIDC token\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write\n      contents: read\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # ... build / pack steps ...\n\n      # Authenticate via OIDC (no API key needed)\n      - name: Install NuGet trusted publish plugin\n        run: dotnet tool install --global NuGetTrustedPublish\n\n      - name: Push with trusted publishing\n        run: dotnet nuget push \"**/*.nupkg\" --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key changes summary\n\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC token (automatic) |\n| No `permissions` block | `id-token: write` required |\n| `--api-key` flag on push | No API key flag needed |\n\n### 3. Clean up\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from **Settings → Secrets** once verified working.\n\nThe critical piece is `permissions: id-token: write` — without it, the GitHub-issued OIDC token won't be available to the NuGet push step. Everything else is removing the old API key plumbing.\n\nWould you like me to create or update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"37a88f8b-32b1-4fa8-aca2-f7ab482874d3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to OIDC trusted publishing in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":542,"requestId":"6C49:28223E:D252B5:10686FB:6A0129C9"},"id":"ad6e0082-6977-4450-a7e7-9c7eac80a756","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:59:02.709Z","parentId":"a95fa7e5-032e-461f-9718-07de9d26730c"}
